x4freetext: -ENERGY SPECTRA OF BREAKUP PROTONS FROM THE D(N,P)2N
14.1 MEV, ENERGY SPREAD OF INCIDENT NEUTRON (FWHM) IS
MEASUREMENT OF BREAKUP PROTON SPECTRA BY COUNTER-
PROPORTIONAL COUNTERS (AS DE/DX COUNTERS) AND A
OVER-ALL ENERGY RESOLUTION FOR BREAKUP PROTON AT 0 DEG
.MEAN ANGLE (IN DATA) WAS CALCULATED BY WEIGHING PROTON
OF PROTONS DUE TO FINITE SIZE OF RADIATOR AND APERTURE
.N-FLUX WAS MONITORED BY ASSOCIATED PARTICLE METHOD
DIFFERENTIAL CROSS SECTION FOR N-P SCATTERING WITH THE
SAME APPARATUS USING A NORMAL POLYETHYLENE RADIATOR OF
5.43 MG/CM THICK, WAS MEASURED FOR CONFIRMATION.
A.P.T. JAPAN CODE CHANGED TO JPN
CORRECTED FOR BACKGROUND COUNTING, CONTRIBUTION OF
RADIATOR USED, CONTRIBUTION OF BREAKUP PROTONS DUE TO
DEGRADED NEUTRONS, AND ENERGY LOSS OF PARTICLES IN
RADIATOR AND ARGON GAS IN THE TELESCOPE.
